{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"carmine-jute-starfish","description":"## Why\nReport §5 found 4/8 post-claim edits were advisories applied only AFTER claim - latency, not blindness: authors defer advisory findings because nothing tells them which are worth applying now. A deterministic pass-4 coaching move that triages advisories is pure coaching (reviewer never writes the plan) and carries no detection risk, so it ships first with no eval gate (per epic gate table) - validated by dogfooding.\n\n## What\nAdd an advisory-triage move to the pass-4 locked move registry: a deterministic coaching note that ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) - no new LLM judgment, template-rendered like every registry move, subject to the existing C1 subject validator. Incorporated directly into the packaged registry (no flags).\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py (MOVE_REGISTRY) + the pass-4/coach seam (src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py) as needed.\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_coach.md only if the picker must learn the move exists.\n- Unit tests pinning deterministic rendering + validator compliance; docs/plan-review-gate.md move-registry section.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The move renders deterministically from recorded finding fields (unit test: same verdict -> byte-identical note) and never emits prescriptive plan text (subject validator test).\n- [ ] Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers, and the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test.\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md documents the move, its ranking rule, and the dogfood expectation (advisory-application latency observed via R7 metrics).\n- [ ] Landed through Gerrit directly in the packaged registry - no config flag.","id":"5dac-c177-56ff-4af4","parent_id":"6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"R6: advisory-triage coaching move (pass-4 registry, ship-first)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784143866501226001,"uuid":"5bf93b2f-7ee8-4b8b-b45a-6ca5feceae38"}